Market Analysis and Insights

Global Raloxifene Market

Raloxifene market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022-2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to account to grow at a CAGR of 8.50% in the above mentioned forecast period.

Raloxifene is a selective estrogen receptor modulator that is used to prevent and treat osteoporosis in high-risk postmenopausal women as well as minimize the incidence of invasive breast cancer. It works to prevent and treat osteoporosis by replicating estrogen's (a female hormone generated by the body) effects on bone density. By inhibiting the effects of estrogen on breast tissue, this drug lowers the risk of developing invasive breast cancer. This could halt the progression of cancers that require estrogen to flourish. Raloxifene is available as a tablet that must be swallowed. It's taken once a day, with or without food. Evista is the brand name for this medication.

The rise in the prevalence of osteoporosis will act a major driver for the expansion of raloxifene market. Furthermore, upsurge in the number of pipe line studies, increasing geriatric population and rising healthcare expenditure are the factors that will expand the raloxifene market. Other factors including changing lifestyle and rising awareness will positively impact the market growth rate. Additionally, advancement in the medical technology, growing government funding and rising level of disposable incomes are the factors that will escalate the growth rate of raloxifene market. Another significant factor influencing the growth rate of market is growing number of cases of breast cancer globally.

Moreover, the rise in the research and development activities and emerging new markets will provide beneficial opportunities for the raloxifene market in the forecast period of 2022-2029. Also, high unmet need of current treatment and developments in healthcare technology will escalate the growth rate of market in future.

However, high cost associated with the product, rising number of approvals by FDA in many countries and lack of infrastructure in low-income countries will impede the growth rate of market. Additionally, side effects of raloxifene such as sweating, joint pain, swelling, leg cramps and flu-like syndrome will hinder the market growth. Less awareness will further challenge the market in the forecast period mentioned above.

